00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:27,387
Employment means
nothing to me, pal.

246
00:20:32,565 --> 00:20:33,565
Lloyd?

247
00:20:55,713 --> 00:20:57,423
David, are you here?

248
00:21:02,303 --> 00:21:04,303
Well, it's nice to see
you made it back.

249
00:21:07,058 --> 00:21:09,808
R.

250
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:10,980
I.

251
00:21:10,978 --> 00:21:13,268
N.

252
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:15,232
G.

253
00:21:16,776 --> 00:21:17,856
Ring?

254
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:20,863
My diamond ring?

255
00:21:23,074 --> 00:21:24,874
You know where it is?

256
00:21:28,204 --> 00:21:29,454
Where?

257
00:21:31,707 --> 00:21:32,787
D.

258
00:21:32,792 --> 00:21:35,502
R.

259
00:21:35,503 --> 00:21:37,213
A.

260
00:21:37,213 --> 00:21:38,593
N.

261
00:21:43,386 --> 00:21:46,506
You mean "drain?"
Like a sink drain?

262
00:21:49,725 --> 00:21:51,685
Which sink? The kitchen?

263
00:21:57,441 --> 00:21:58,861
The bathroom.

264
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:03,780
Thanks, David.

265
00:22:45,406 --> 00:22:49,906
Oh! Ow. Darn.

266
00:22:50,453 --> 00:22:52,003
There goes my nail.

267
00:23:40,461 --> 00:23:44,051
Jesus Christ, don't ever sneak
up on me again. Fuck!

268
00:23:44,048 --> 00:23:46,088
Shit.

269
00:23:46,801 --> 00:23:48,181
Fuck.

270
00:23:52,723 --> 00:23:54,143
What are you doing home?

271
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,640
I live here.

272
00:23:56,644 --> 00:23:58,104
What are you up to?

273
00:24:00,398 --> 00:24:04,148
I found my ring. Remember the one
that I lost when we moved in? See?

274
00:24:04,527 --> 00:24:07,697
And that's such a monumental event
that you started swearing?

275
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:09,737
What?

276
00:24:10,282 --> 00:24:13,162
Your language, babe. I think
"gosh" and "darn" are

277
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:15,620
the strongest words I've
ever heard you use.

278
00:24:17,289 --> 00:24:19,209
And when did you take up plumbing?

279
00:24:20,709 --> 00:24:25,089
You're never gonna believe
this. David, he told-

280
00:24:25,089 --> 00:24:26,549
Uh, David who?

281
00:24:27,466 --> 00:24:30,336
You remember David. The
spirit of the little boy?

282
00:24:30,344 --> 00:24:32,684
Oh, I don't need to
hear this shit now.

283
00:24:38,561 --> 00:24:42,481
Jim! What's-What's the matter?

284
00:24:47,278 --> 00:24:51,408
They closed the site early today.
There was an accident, and...

285
00:24:55,035 --> 00:24:57,285
Lloyd, uh...

286
00:24:59,123 --> 00:25:00,713
Lloyd got killed.

287
00:25:05,087 --> 00:25:07,877
Oh, god, what happened?

288
00:25:08,466 --> 00:25:10,126
There was a load of sheet rock, and it

289
00:25:10,134 --> 00:25:17,314
wasn't secured properly,
and it... fell.

290
00:25:20,102 --> 00:25:26,862
I've never liked you doing
that job. It is so dangerous.

291
00:25:28,944 --> 00:25:31,114
Everything is dangerous.

292
00:26:42,101 --> 00:26:44,811
[RETCHING]

293
00:27:25,894 --> 00:27:27,484
Mr. Morar?

294
00:27:30,649 --> 00:27:32,069
My name is Duherst.

295
00:27:32,818 --> 00:27:34,608
Lieutenant Duherst.

296
00:27:35,154 --> 00:27:37,914
- Police?
- Homicide.

297
00:27:38,657 --> 00:27:40,867
I didn't know Fairfield had
a homicide division.

298
00:27:41,243 --> 00:27:44,543
I'm it! I'm also the bomb squad
and the truancy division.

299
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,910
- Do you like magic?
- What?

300
00:27:47,499 --> 00:27:51,499
Magic, you know. Card tricks, sawing
ladies in half. Magic.

301
00:27:53,005 --> 00:27:55,085
Yeah, I guess.

302
00:27:55,090 --> 00:27:57,130
Me too. I always wanted
to be a magician.

303
00:27:57,134 --> 00:28:00,854
I don't have the hands for it, though.
Not, uh, dextrous enough.

304
00:28:00,846 --> 00:28:05,176
- Then how do you defuse bombs?
- I don't know.

305
00:28:05,184 --> 00:28:07,814
No one's ever planted a bomb here.

306
00:28:09,063 --> 00:28:10,613
What can I do for you, lieutenant?

307
00:28:11,190 --> 00:28:13,940
I'm investigating Mr.
Salvador's death.

308
00:28:16,070 --> 00:28:18,030
You ever been to Vegas?

309
00:28:18,989 --> 00:28:20,699
No. Why?

310
00:28:21,492 --> 00:28:24,292
They got these two guys
there, Sigmund and Roy.

311
00:28:24,286 --> 00:28:27,076
I mean, they are the best
magicians I have ever

312
00:28:27,081 --> 00:28:28,501
seen, without a doubt.

313
00:28:29,583 --> 00:28:32,003
I mean, they do some
really amazing things.

314
00:28:34,088 --> 00:28:36,708
You know, there's only
one thing I like better

315
00:28:36,715 --> 00:28:38,465
than seeing a good magic trick.

316
00:28:39,051 --> 00:28:41,721
It's trying to figure
out how it was done.

317
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:47,476
Lieutenant, we're not really talking
about magic, here, are we?

318
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:50,811
No.

319
00:28:52,648 --> 00:28:54,818
I believe Mr. Salvador was murdered.

320
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:58,027
The ropes holding the sheet
rock on the scaffolding

321
00:28:58,028 --> 00:29:00,278
were cut, apparently with
some sort of hatchet.

322
00:29:01,532 --> 00:29:03,872
- Are you sure?
- I'm afraid so.

323
00:29:05,244 --> 00:29:06,834
Did he have any enemies?

324
00:29:08,163 --> 00:29:10,963
No. None that I know of.

325
00:29:12,292 --> 00:29:15,132
I understand that you were with him
when the sheet rock fell.

326
00:29:15,129 --> 00:29:17,049
Now, is there any
chance that the killer

327
00:29:17,047 --> 00:29:18,547
could have been aiming for you?

328
00:29:19,967 --> 00:29:23,507
- I don't think so.
- Are there any other witnesses?

329
00:29:25,472 --> 00:29:27,892
No. No, I'm afraid not.

330
00:29:29,226 --> 00:29:31,886
And you lost your hatchet
that same day.

331
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:35,652
I lost my hammer.

332
00:29:35,649 --> 00:29:38,399
But it has a blade on one side, right?

333
00:29:41,488 --> 00:29:42,948
Have you found it yet?

334
00:29:45,576 --> 00:29:48,536
No. No, I had to buy a new one.

335
00:29:49,955 --> 00:29:52,365
Just vanished into thin air, huh?

336
00:29:54,001 --> 00:29:55,331
Nothing up my sleeve.

337
00:29:58,213 --> 00:29:59,463
Touche.

338
00:30:01,008 --> 00:30:05,338
I'm sorry for intruding here.

339
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:14,649
Jim, you didn't tell me
you were with him.

340
00:30:16,231 --> 00:30:17,821
I didn't think it was important.

341
00:30:17,816 --> 00:30:20,226
It is important, it could
have been you!

342
00:30:20,235 --> 00:30:26,235
Hey, it was just an accident, that's
all. It was just an accident.

343
00:30:27,493 --> 00:30:28,873
Can we go?

344
00:30:33,665 --> 00:30:36,745
LINDA: Well, the lieutenant's
not too sure about that.

345
00:30:37,961 --> 00:30:39,421
And neither am I.

346
00:30:42,132 --> 00:30:45,472
David? Did you cause that
accident at the site?

347
00:30:49,681 --> 00:30:52,271
David, don't lie to me.

348
00:31:00,192 --> 00:31:02,532
Are you still angry at Jim?

349
00:31:04,822 --> 00:31:06,362
David?

350
00:31:10,077 --> 00:31:11,117
David.

351
00:31:15,582 --> 00:31:23,582
[PHONE RINGING]

352
00:31:28,095 --> 00:31:29,255
Hello?

353
00:31:29,263 --> 00:31:30,643
Where were you?

354
00:31:30,639 --> 00:31:31,849
(LINDA, OVER TELEPHONE) What?

355
00:31:31,849 --> 00:31:34,849
You were supposed to bring
my Ouija by class yesterday.

356
00:31:35,435 --> 00:31:38,345
God, I am so sorry,
I completely forgot.

357
00:31:38,355 --> 00:31:40,605
I went to the funeral with Jim.

358
00:31:41,483 --> 00:31:44,403
Oh. Yeah, of course, uh...

359
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:47,574
Well, how's he taking it?

360
00:31:48,824 --> 00:31:50,284
Well, he's sleeping right now.

361
00:31:50,659 --> 00:31:52,259
(BRANDON, OVER TELEPHONE)
Kind of figures.

362
00:31:52,452 --> 00:31:54,082
Brandon, that's not even fair.

363
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:58,366
Isn't it? Tell me, did he
cry at the funeral?

364
00:32:03,130 --> 00:32:04,800
Face it, Linda.

365
00:32:04,798 --> 00:32:07,048
The man has ice in his
veins. I've known him

366
00:32:07,050 --> 00:32:09,260
since he was seven and I've
never seen him cry once.

367
00:32:09,261 --> 00:32:11,301
Not once. Not for anybody or anything.

368
00:32:19,438 --> 00:32:24,528
Brandon? How many times
have you contacted David?

369
00:32:24,526 --> 00:32:25,686
David?

370
00:32:27,154 --> 00:32:29,864
Quite a few times. Why?

371
00:32:30,741 --> 00:32:32,491
Have you ever seen him get that angry?

372
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:37,615
No, never. Look, did we just change
subjects when I wasn't looking?

373
00:32:38,248 --> 00:32:44,338
Brandon, I've been getting a little
worried. I've been using the Ouija.

374
00:32:44,338 --> 00:32:45,338
Alone?

375
00:32:45,839 --> 00:32:47,089
Yeah. Why?

376
00:32:47,549 --> 00:32:49,299
Linda, listen to me.
[CLICK]

377
00:32:51,595 --> 00:32:55,095
Hello? Hello?

378
00:32:55,766 --> 00:32:56,966
Brandon?

379
00:32:57,351 --> 00:32:59,101
- Hello?
- Hello.

380
00:33:00,437 --> 00:33:04,317
God damn it, how many times have
I told you not to sneak up on me?

381
00:33:04,316 --> 00:33:06,646
Look, I'm sorry, next
time I'll wear a bell.

382
00:33:06,652 --> 00:33:09,322
Why don't you just rattle your
fucking head next time?

383
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,660
What the hell's eating you?

384
00:33:16,203 --> 00:33:17,873
I don't know.

385
00:33:20,165 --> 00:33:23,535
I don't know, I'm so scared.
I feel like I'm going crazy.

386
00:33:28,548 --> 00:33:29,878
It's alright.

387
00:33:29,883 --> 00:33:31,593
It's gonna be alright.

388
00:33:42,187 --> 00:33:43,847
I'm pregnant.

389
00:33:51,321 --> 00:33:53,071
Are you sure?

390
00:33:53,907 --> 00:33:55,867
I mean, did you see a doctor?

391
00:33:58,829 --> 00:34:01,289
I already know.

392
00:34:01,832 --> 00:34:03,752
I have an appointment on Monday.

393
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:05,840
And I've been having morning
sickness all week.

394
00:34:10,841 --> 00:34:12,551
Well, no wonder.

395
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,678
No wonder you're a nervous wreck.

396
00:34:18,181 --> 00:34:22,561
You're not going crazy. You're
just becoming a mother.

397
00:34:26,106 --> 00:34:28,356
Granted, it's almost the same thing.

398
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:30,110
You're not upset?

399
00:34:33,155 --> 00:34:37,575
No. No. Of course not.

400
00:34:39,619 --> 00:34:41,249
God, I love you.

401
00:34:44,458 --> 00:34:46,248
I know.

402
00:34:52,174 --> 00:34:54,264
And you love me.

403
00:34:56,053 --> 00:35:01,773
Even though you don't
know it, I know it.

404
00:35:22,621 --> 00:35:28,001
[TUNELESS SINGING]

405
00:35:42,265 --> 00:35:47,185
[SINGING CONTINUES]

406
00:36:28,478 --> 00:36:30,858
I'm giving the board back
to Brandon today.

407
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:38,070
I've already made up my mind, David.
There's nothing you can do about it.

408
00:37:12,856 --> 00:37:14,816
Oh my god.

409
00:37:32,834 --> 00:37:36,504
[SCREAMING]

410
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:48,559
Hey. Hey. Do you know
Jim Morar? Where is he?

411
00:38:21,549 --> 00:38:23,089
What are you doing here?

412
00:38:23,093 --> 00:38:25,553
I tried to call but your
phone was dead.

413
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:29,218
And you drove all the way
out here to tell me that?

414
00:38:29,933 --> 00:38:33,393
No. I want to ask you
something about Linda.

415
00:38:34,604 --> 00:38:36,274
You want to know if she snores.

416
00:38:37,482 --> 00:38:38,772
I should've known better.

417
00:38:38,775 --> 00:38:42,945
Hey. Hey! Jesus, man, you used
to have a sense of humor.

418
00:38:42,946 --> 00:38:45,986
Okay, can you be serious
for one minute, please?

419
00:38:46,658 --> 00:38:48,158
I'll give it a shot.

420
00:38:48,952 --> 00:38:50,832
Has Linda been acting
strange lately?

421
00:38:51,329 --> 00:38:53,749
She hasn't been to a single
one of her classes all week.

422
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:55,170
What do you mean, "strange?"

423
00:38:56,626 --> 00:38:59,746
I mean nervous tension,
insomnia, nausea,

424
00:38:59,754 --> 00:39:01,964
any kind of erratic behavior?

425
00:39:02,924 --> 00:39:04,224
How did you know?

426
00:39:06,052 --> 00:39:07,932
Has she been swearing a lot?

427
00:39:10,515 --> 00:39:11,925
Like a truck driver.

428
00:39:12,559 --> 00:39:14,689
I think Linda's been using my Ouija.

429
00:39:15,687 --> 00:39:17,097
No.

430
00:39:18,356 --> 00:39:20,266
[LAUGHING]

431
00:39:21,276 --> 00:39:26,656
Alright. Alright, I know you
think this is a crock of shit.

432
00:39:26,865 --> 00:39:29,155
But just bear with me
for a minute, please.

433
00:39:30,118 --> 00:39:31,118
Okay.

434
00:39:32,162 --> 00:39:35,122
Okay. When someone
uses a Ouija alone,

435
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:38,293
like Linda, she's very
susceptible to the

436
00:39:38,293 --> 00:39:42,303
spirits she contacts. And the wrong
spirit will take advantage of this.

437
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:46,511
At first, he'll be extremely
helpful and friendly.

438
00:39:47,469 --> 00:39:50,259
So that she's lured into using
the board more and more.

439
00:39:50,764 --> 00:39:53,184
Pretty soon all she wants
to do is use the board.

440
00:39:53,600 --> 00:39:56,980
Everything else, like going to
classes, becomes unimportant.

441
00:39:59,064 --> 00:40:01,114
This is called progressive entrapment.

442
00:40:03,485 --> 00:40:06,815
When she reaches this
stage, the spirit changes.

443
00:40:07,572 --> 00:40:10,032
He starts to frighten
and terrorize her.

444
00:40:10,033 --> 00:40:13,493
Gradually breaking down
her resistance. And

445
00:40:13,495 --> 00:40:16,955
once that's done, he's
able to possess her.

446
00:40:22,462 --> 00:40:28,092
So, what you're telling me is
that I'm living with Linda Blair.

447
00:40:28,093 --> 00:40:30,643
Dammit, Jim, I'm serious!

448
00:40:32,305 --> 00:40:35,305
I know. That's what makes it so funny.

449
00:40:36,059 --> 00:40:38,189
I thought you were an atheist, man.

450
00:40:38,603 --> 00:40:40,983
Look, I'm not saying
that it's a demon.

451
00:40:40,980 --> 00:40:42,980
Just the spirit of someone evil.

452
00:40:42,982 --> 00:40:45,862
Evil when he was alive and
evil now that he's dead

453
00:40:48,154 --> 00:40:50,204
I want to bring a medium
by your apartment

454
00:40:50,198 --> 00:40:52,238
as soon as possible
to exorcise the spirit.

455
00:40:52,742 --> 00:40:54,162
[SCOFFING]

456
00:40:56,955 --> 00:40:58,115
You're serious.

457
00:40:58,540 --> 00:40:59,540
Jim.

458
00:40:59,916 --> 00:41:02,576
How do you think I knew all
those things about Linda?

459
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:05,955
Those are all symptoms of
progressive entrapment.

460
00:41:06,798 --> 00:41:09,508
They're also all symptoms
of pregnancy.

461
00:41:10,718 --> 00:41:11,718
What?

462
00:41:12,512 --> 00:41:13,802
Linda's pregnant.

463
00:41:14,222 --> 00:41:15,722
I'm going to be a father.

464
00:41:17,892 --> 00:41:19,392
Terrific.

465
00:41:20,353 --> 00:41:25,363
Come on, Brandon. I mean,
can't you be happy for us?

466
00:41:27,068 --> 00:41:28,358
You gonna marry her?

467
00:41:31,114 --> 00:41:32,114
Yeah.

468
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:34,157
Of course.

469
00:41:35,702 --> 00:41:37,662
You don't even love her.

470
00:41:38,788 --> 00:41:41,998
Let me tell you something. You
haven't talked to me in two years.

471
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:44,880
So don't stand there
and tell me how I feel.

472
00:41:48,756 --> 00:41:51,926
I know you better than
you think I do, Jim.

473
00:41:52,677 --> 00:41:56,387
I knew why you dropped out
of med school, does Linda?

474
00:41:56,389 --> 00:41:59,179
Because you knew you'd
make a lousy doctor.

475
00:41:59,184 --> 00:42:02,314
Because you're not capable of giving
a shit about anyone but yourself.

476
00:42:02,312 --> 00:42:02,982
Shut up, Brandon.

477
00:42:02,979 --> 00:42:05,229
And when you get tired
of Linda you're gonna

478
00:42:05,231 --> 00:42:07,571
walk away from her too,
just like with school.

479
00:42:07,567 --> 00:42:08,317
Shut up, Brandon.

480
00:42:08,318 --> 00:42:10,608
Just like you did with your
parents, just like with-

481
00:42:10,612 --> 00:42:11,702
Shut up!

482
00:42:13,198 --> 00:42:14,568
- Jim?
- What?

483
00:42:16,242 --> 00:42:18,622
There's a phone call for you
in the foreman's trailer.

484
00:42:19,746 --> 00:42:22,956
- Take a message, I'm busy.
- It's your landlady, man.

485
00:42:22,957 --> 00:42:24,627
It's something about Linda.

486
00:42:28,254 --> 00:42:29,254
She alright?

487
00:42:47,357 --> 00:42:48,317
Hello?

488
00:42:48,316 --> 00:42:50,226
(OVER TELEPHONE)
Jim, this is Mrs. Boses.

489
00:42:50,235 --> 00:42:52,065
Is Linda alright?

490
00:42:52,070 --> 00:42:55,700
Well, she's fine now but she
was scared awfully bad.

491
00:42:56,282 --> 00:42:57,912
Well, let me talk to
her. Is she there?

492
00:42:58,368 --> 00:42:59,448
Yeah. Just a minute.

493
00:43:02,956 --> 00:43:05,416
- Jim?
- I'm right here, babe.

494
00:43:07,293 --> 00:43:09,843
- It was David.
- David?

495
00:43:11,089 --> 00:43:12,089
Yeah.

496
00:43:13,341 --> 00:43:15,591
Jim, he used to be so nice, but-

497
00:43:18,513 --> 00:43:20,643
I don't know, I'm just so scared.

498
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:24,480
It's alright, babe. I'm
on my way home.

499
00:43:25,395 --> 00:43:27,185
And I'll take care of it, I promise.

500
00:43:28,231 --> 00:43:29,611
Alright?

501
00:43:29,607 --> 00:43:30,727
Okay.

502
