01:04:42,546 --> 01:04:45,126
the life often-year-old David Simpson
early yesterday morning.

761
01:04:45,632 --> 01:04:49,682
Funeral services for David, the only
child of John and Betty Simpson,

762
01:04:49,678 --> 01:04:52,348
will be held this Saturday at the
Green Meadows Cemetery.

763
01:04:55,141 --> 01:04:57,231
Well, now we know David's
telling the truth.

764
01:04:57,978 --> 01:05:00,098
We still don't know why
he's terrorizing Linda.

765
01:05:02,023 --> 01:05:03,523
How do we find that out?

766
01:05:07,779 --> 01:05:09,149
We ask his parents.

767
01:05:15,787 --> 01:05:20,167
Damn it! There's not one listing
for John or Betty Simpson.

768
01:05:24,546 --> 01:05:27,836
Did the article say David was buried
at the Green Meadows Cemetery?

769
01:05:28,258 --> 01:05:29,428
Yeah. So?

770
01:05:30,510 --> 01:05:33,180
So maybe the caretaker's got
their address on an invoice.

771
01:05:50,614 --> 01:05:52,624
Jesus, don't do that to me, alright?

772
01:05:53,074 --> 01:05:54,374
Sorry, man.

773
01:05:56,036 --> 01:05:58,406
Look, nobody's home.
Place is locked up.

774
01:05:59,623 --> 01:06:00,623
Oh, damn it.

775
01:06:01,041 --> 01:06:03,291
I guess we're just gonna have
to come back tomorrow.

776
01:06:04,711 --> 01:06:08,131
Well, as long as we're here, I'm
gonna check out David's grave.

777
01:06:09,090 --> 01:06:10,090
Why?

778
01:06:11,426 --> 01:06:12,756
Why not?

779
01:06:12,761 --> 01:06:14,431
No, Jim, don't!

780
01:06:25,398 --> 01:06:27,608
I've got a very bad
feeling about this.

781
01:06:36,785 --> 01:06:39,535
Oh, god, I've got a bad
feeling about this.

782
01:06:54,886 --> 01:06:55,886
Jim?

783
01:06:59,849 --> 01:07:00,849
Jim?

784
01:07:01,309 --> 01:07:02,639
Where are you?

785
01:07:03,144 --> 01:07:04,814
[OWLS HOOTING]

786
01:08:36,946 --> 01:08:38,606
Whoa!

787
01:08:39,240 --> 01:08:40,490
Shit.

788
01:08:41,493 --> 01:08:42,623
Oh, god.

789
01:08:42,619 --> 01:08:44,159
You scared the shit out of me.

790
01:08:44,662 --> 01:08:47,082
Shut up, just shut up.
You're gonna get

791
01:08:47,082 --> 01:08:49,332
us both arrested for grave robbery.

792
01:08:49,334 --> 01:08:51,294
Where were you?

793
01:08:51,836 --> 01:08:53,246
I found someone I want you to meet.

794
01:08:54,255 --> 01:08:55,255
Who?

795
01:08:56,424 --> 01:08:57,934
David's parents.

796
01:09:00,970 --> 01:09:02,510
Look at the date, man.

797
01:09:04,224 --> 01:09:06,434
David's parents died on the same day.

798
01:09:06,434 --> 01:09:08,394
Less than two weeks ago.

799
01:09:08,394 --> 01:09:10,774
Must have been some
kind of an accident.

800
01:09:13,983 --> 01:09:15,193
What if it wasn't?

801
01:09:20,698 --> 01:09:22,618
BRANDON: I'm going to
try and get some sleep.

802
01:09:23,576 --> 01:09:25,656
Gotta get out to the dock
first thing in the morning.

803
01:09:27,497 --> 01:09:29,997
I don't suppose you have an
extra toothbrush in that bag.

804
01:09:32,293 --> 01:09:33,383
I'm afraid not.

805
01:09:34,546 --> 01:09:37,296
Damn, I hate talking to ghosts
with plaque on my teeth.

806
01:09:40,176 --> 01:09:42,086
[LAUGHING]

807
01:09:43,763 --> 01:09:45,183
A little psychic humor.

808
01:09:48,184 --> 01:09:50,064
God, why are we laughing?

809
01:09:51,646 --> 01:09:53,516
It helps us forget how scared we are.

810
01:10:01,656 --> 01:10:02,866
What happened to us, man?

811
01:10:06,786 --> 01:10:08,156
We used to be like brothers.

812
01:10:12,876 --> 01:10:14,496
I don't know. Things change.

813
01:10:15,086 --> 01:10:16,296
People change.

814
01:10:18,756 --> 01:10:20,876
I didn't steal her from
you. You know that.

815
01:10:23,469 --> 01:10:24,549
I know.

816
01:10:25,346 --> 01:10:28,176
It's just that every time I see the
two of you together, I go crazy.

817
01:10:30,101 --> 01:10:32,521
I start saying stupid
things and I can't stop.

818
01:10:34,480 --> 01:10:36,860
I tell myself, "Brandon, stop
being such an asshole."

819
01:10:36,858 --> 01:10:39,818
Then my mouth pops open and
out comes another stupid quip.

820
01:10:41,279 --> 01:10:43,359
You're still in love with her.

821
01:10:52,874 --> 01:10:54,374
I envy you that.

822
01:10:55,168 --> 01:10:57,538
You remember what you said
about me quitting med school?

823
01:10:58,379 --> 01:10:59,959
Jim, I'm sorry, I didn't mean that.

824
01:11:00,298 --> 01:11:02,008
No, no, you were right.

825
01:11:04,594 --> 01:11:07,104
You know what I'm afraid of
more than anything else?

826
01:11:09,599 --> 01:11:11,349
That I'll never be able
to love anyone.

827
01:11:12,644 --> 01:11:15,774
And that I'm gonna end up spending
the rest of my life alone.

828
01:11:25,156 --> 01:11:27,526
If I had any real guts
I'd get out of her life

829
01:11:27,533 --> 01:11:29,413
before she wastes any more time on me.

830
01:11:37,377 --> 01:11:38,747
So tell me.

831
01:11:42,215 --> 01:11:44,375
What does she see in you
that she didn't see in me?

832
01:11:45,927 --> 01:11:47,047
I make her laugh.

833
01:11:48,054 --> 01:11:49,054
So did I.

834
01:11:49,555 --> 01:11:52,465
Yeah. But only in the bedroom.

835
01:11:59,565 --> 01:12:01,525
[LAUGHING]

836
01:12:11,369 --> 01:12:13,869
You really are an asshole,
you know that?

837
01:12:14,622 --> 01:12:16,002
Yeah.

838
01:12:21,504 --> 01:12:25,424
GHOSTLY VOICE:
Linda.

839
01:13:13,639 --> 01:13:17,309
GHOSTLY VOICE: Linda. Come here.

840
01:13:33,785 --> 01:13:35,035
[SCREAMING]

841
01:13:39,957 --> 01:13:41,497
- What'd you get?
- Take it.

842
01:13:41,876 --> 01:13:42,876
Let's go.

843
01:13:47,382 --> 01:13:48,552
Oh, man.

844
01:13:48,883 --> 01:13:52,393
- Haven't we seen enough of these?
- We're gonna need it to contact David.

845
01:13:53,679 --> 01:13:56,139
Man, I got a real bad
feeling about this.

846
01:14:01,104 --> 01:14:03,984
What are you doing, man? I thought
we had to put this thing on our knees.

847
01:14:04,482 --> 01:14:05,482
Not this time.

848
01:14:06,317 --> 01:14:08,317
Since this is where
David died, contact

849
01:14:08,319 --> 01:14:10,199
with the spirit should be very strong.

850
01:14:11,114 --> 01:14:12,114
Not too strong, I hope.

851
01:14:12,407 --> 01:14:15,407
Don't worry. If I'm right
about Linda being his

852
01:14:15,410 --> 01:14:17,490
portal, she's too far away
for him to reach us.

853
01:14:18,204 --> 01:14:20,164
What if you're wrong and
the Ouija's the portal?

854
01:14:20,164 --> 01:14:22,374
We're gonna be opening the
door if we use this thing.

855
01:14:23,042 --> 01:14:24,002
I'm not wrong.

856
01:14:24,001 --> 01:14:27,501
Linda is his portal. David can't hurt
us here, we're too far away.

857
01:14:27,922 --> 01:14:30,172
Besides, he can't do anything
while she's sleeping.

858
01:14:30,675 --> 01:14:32,125
She's under sedation, right?

859
01:14:33,386 --> 01:14:34,386
Yeah.

860
01:14:36,931 --> 01:14:37,931
Linda?

861
01:14:38,474 --> 01:14:41,144
I think you should stay and let
us run some more tests.

862
01:14:41,144 --> 01:14:44,404
Oh, no, I feel fine. I just
want to go home now.

863
01:14:45,606 --> 01:14:46,606
Thanks.

864
01:14:51,112 --> 01:14:53,572
David, why are you terrorizing Linda?

865
01:15:00,997 --> 01:15:03,707
"N-O?" N-O-what?

866
01:15:08,504 --> 01:15:09,214
"T."

867
01:15:09,213 --> 01:15:10,923
"N-O-T." Not?

868
01:15:11,257 --> 01:15:13,507
David, do you mean you're
not terrorizing Linda?

869
01:15:17,138 --> 01:15:18,138
Then who is?

870
01:15:31,736 --> 01:15:34,316
Evil. What the hell
does that mean?

871
01:15:35,907 --> 01:15:37,027
I don't know.

872
01:15:38,659 --> 01:15:40,119
Wait a minute.

873
01:15:41,078 --> 01:15:45,998
David. You were at Jim's
party, weren't you?

874
01:15:49,253 --> 01:15:50,713
And you flattened my tire?

875
01:15:55,218 --> 01:15:59,388
David, now, this is very important.
Please tell us the truth.

876
01:16:00,806 --> 01:16:04,306
Did you kill Lloyd at
the construction site?

877
01:16:08,856 --> 01:16:10,686
And you didn't kill Zarabeth?

878
01:16:11,901 --> 01:16:14,321
But you did speak to
us through her.

879
01:16:17,907 --> 01:16:19,157
No.

880
01:16:20,284 --> 01:16:21,834
Then who the hell did we talk to?

881
01:16:36,425 --> 01:16:38,215
Again with the evil.

882
01:16:38,469 --> 01:16:40,349
Wait a minute, wait a minute.
I think I have it.

883
01:16:41,180 --> 01:16:42,180
David.

884
01:16:43,099 --> 01:16:45,599
Is this evil another spirit?

885
01:16:50,147 --> 01:16:53,277
Is this spirit powerful? Did it force
you out of Jim's apartment?

886
01:16:56,654 --> 01:16:58,574
Is this spirit's name Malfeitor?

887
01:17:02,034 --> 01:17:04,374
Then Linda never actually
contacted you

888
01:17:04,370 --> 01:17:06,500
all the time she was using my Ouija.

889
01:17:09,584 --> 01:17:12,294
Alright, then who's Malfeitor?

890
01:17:12,295 --> 01:17:14,165
That's what we're gonna find out.

891
01:17:15,339 --> 01:17:19,759
David? Who is Malfeitor?

892
01:17:34,984 --> 01:17:35,984
"Her?" Who is "her?"

893
01:17:36,569 --> 01:17:37,779
David, do you mean Linda?

894
01:17:39,488 --> 01:17:40,948
Well, then who is "her?"

895
01:17:45,411 --> 01:17:46,371
What's wrong?

896
01:17:46,370 --> 01:17:48,580
I don't know, he's agitated.
Be careful.

897
01:17:49,165 --> 01:17:52,375
David, are you alright?
What's the matter?

898
01:17:53,919 --> 01:17:54,919
Hey.

899
01:17:55,546 --> 01:17:57,756
Didn't you say they
were lousy spellers?

900
01:17:59,091 --> 01:18:01,841
David, did you misspell the word?

901
01:18:06,265 --> 01:18:08,885
Alright. Okay.

902
01:18:11,312 --> 01:18:13,692
Just try again.

903
01:18:13,689 --> 01:18:16,069
One more time, slowly.

904
01:18:17,568 --> 01:18:19,068
Who is Malfeitor?

905
01:18:24,075 --> 01:18:25,075
H.

906
01:18:28,954 --> 01:18:29,954
E.

907
01:18:33,292 --> 01:18:34,292
R.

908
01:18:41,467 --> 01:18:42,507
What happened?

909
01:18:43,344 --> 01:18:44,344
I lost him.

910
01:18:44,887 --> 01:18:46,967
It happens sometimes. David.

911
01:18:48,849 --> 01:18:51,019
- Can't you get him back?
- I don't know! David!

912
01:18:51,644 --> 01:18:54,814
- What is he trying to spell here?
- I don't know! David?

913
01:18:54,814 --> 01:18:59,324
H-E-R-E. Here!

914
01:19:01,153 --> 01:19:02,743
Malfeitor is here.

915
01:19:03,489 --> 01:19:04,889
But he can't be, that would mean...

916
01:19:25,803 --> 01:19:28,933
[GASPING]

917
01:19:40,901 --> 01:19:41,901
Jim.

918
01:20:51,096 --> 01:20:52,096
Brandon?

919
01:21:02,566 --> 01:21:03,686
Brandon!

920
01:21:49,280 --> 01:21:52,570
Oh! Jesus!

921
01:22:00,207 --> 01:22:01,207
Oh, god.

922
01:22:05,421 --> 01:22:08,131
Oh. Oh, god.

923
01:22:10,009 --> 01:22:11,299
Oh, god.

924
01:22:16,181 --> 01:22:20,481
[CRYING]

925
01:24:13,132 --> 01:24:14,132
David?

926
01:24:19,972 --> 01:24:21,062
David, where are you?

927
01:24:23,600 --> 01:24:25,230
David, what have you done with Jim?

928
01:24:26,562 --> 01:24:28,602
David, answer me, goddammit.

929
01:24:53,797 --> 01:24:55,797
Bastard.

930
01:25:10,189 --> 01:25:12,819
Carlos Malfeitor was
a fairly notorious

931
01:25:12,816 --> 01:25:14,526
mass murderer in his day.

932
01:25:15,235 --> 01:25:19,235
He killed nine people. Chopped
them all up with an axe.

933
01:25:20,282 --> 01:25:23,162
Whatever happened to him?
Is he still alive?

934
01:25:23,160 --> 01:25:26,620
No, the police finally caught
up to him around 1930.

935
01:25:26,622 --> 01:25:29,172
Shot him down in his own home.

936
01:25:32,836 --> 01:25:33,836
There it is.

937
01:25:42,679 --> 01:25:43,679
Hello?

938
01:25:43,931 --> 01:25:46,021
Yes, I'd like to speak
to Linda Brewster.

939
01:25:46,016 --> 01:25:48,726
She's a patient in room 310.

940
01:25:48,727 --> 01:25:51,437
No! No. 375.

941
01:25:52,815 --> 01:25:54,225
It's an emergency!

942
01:25:56,401 --> 01:25:58,571
What? When?

943
01:26:18,132 --> 01:26:21,512
[SCREAMING]

944
01:27:01,300 --> 01:27:02,880
[SCREAMING]

945
01:27:46,178 --> 01:27:48,638
[SCREAMING]

946
01:27:48,639 --> 01:27:50,559
[GUTTURAL ROARING]

947
01:27:58,982 --> 01:28:00,072
Linda?

948
01:28:09,493 --> 01:28:11,793
Jesus Christ.

949
01:28:28,345 --> 01:28:29,635
Linda, I'm trying to help you.

950
01:28:30,597 --> 01:28:33,137
Fine. Then stop moving.

951
01:29:30,073 --> 01:29:31,533
Go ahead, James.

952
01:29:32,617 --> 01:29:34,077
What are you waiting for?

953
01:29:34,077 --> 01:29:35,367
Linda...

954
01:29:35,787 --> 01:29:36,787
I love you.

955
01:29:42,669 --> 01:29:43,669
Jim?

956
01:29:47,132 --> 01:29:48,132
God, Linda, I...

957
01:29:48,300 --> 01:29:51,760
It's not that easy, James.

958
01:30:06,985 --> 01:30:08,435
Don't move, asshole!

959
01:30:08,987 --> 01:30:11,697
The rest of you people go back
down to your apartments, now!

960
01:30:16,328 --> 01:30:18,968
I understand you left quite a mess
up there in Big Bear, Mr. Morar.

961
01:30:20,207 --> 01:30:21,707
Duherst, listen.

962
01:30:22,959 --> 01:30:24,169
It's not what you think.

963
01:30:25,670 --> 01:30:27,550
Listen to me. Don't...

964
01:30:30,842 --> 01:30:32,392
Mrs. Brewster, can you stand?

965
01:30:45,857 --> 01:30:48,317
You won't kill her, James.

966
01:30:48,610 --> 01:30:50,070
I'll just shoot her in the leg.

967
01:30:52,531 --> 01:30:54,241
That won't change anything.

968
01:30:56,368 --> 01:30:57,658
It'll buy us some time.

969
01:30:59,955 --> 01:31:02,455
Time to fight you. Time for
Linda to close the portal.

970
01:31:04,835 --> 01:31:06,665
Only you can do that, James.

971
01:31:07,170 --> 01:31:08,170
Put it down.

972
01:31:10,090 --> 01:31:11,170
Put it down!

973
01:31:18,432 --> 01:31:21,482
You're so... smart.

974
01:31:26,314 --> 01:31:28,614
You haven't figured it out
yet, have you, James?

975
01:31:32,696 --> 01:31:33,856
You're the portal.

976
01:31:34,656 --> 01:31:35,696
Not Linda.

977
01:31:37,868 --> 01:31:39,238
You're the one I opened.

978
01:31:39,953 --> 01:31:42,663
You're the one I terrorized
by torturing

979
01:31:42,664 --> 01:31:44,834
Linda and killing your friends.

980
01:31:47,794 --> 01:31:51,384
And it's mine as long as you live.

981
01:31:52,466 --> 01:31:53,466
Bullshit.

982
01:31:54,551 --> 01:31:56,431
Bullshit, you tried to kill me.

983
01:31:57,387 --> 01:32:01,677
No. Just to scare you.

984
01:32:03,226 --> 01:32:04,806
You're the portal, James.

985
01:32:08,732 --> 01:32:12,112
Want to save Linda? That's right.

986
01:32:13,361 --> 01:32:16,361
You've got the means right there in
your hands. Go ahead, James.

987
01:32:19,201 --> 01:32:20,831
Close the portal.

988
01:32:22,662 --> 01:32:24,002
But you won't.

989
01:32:28,627 --> 01:32:29,707
You can't.

990
01:32:31,296 --> 01:32:36,876
You don't love her that much.
Not that much.

991
01:32:41,515 --> 01:32:42,595
Linda.

992
01:32:43,600 --> 01:32:45,180
Is she worth it, James?

993
01:32:47,687 --> 01:32:52,267
Is anybody really worth it?
Think about it.

994
01:32:58,740 --> 01:32:59,740
Jim, don't!

995
01:33:57,465 --> 01:34:00,085
I now pronounce you man and wife.

996
01:34:00,093 --> 01:34:02,303
You may kiss the bride.

997
01:34:04,347 --> 01:34:06,967
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

998
01:34:25,493 --> 01:34:27,163
Look what I found.

999
01:34:31,207 --> 01:34:36,497
A Ouija board. Gee, I haven't seen
one of these since I was a kid.

1000
01:34:36,504 --> 01:34:38,514
I didn't know they've
been around that long.

1001
01:34:41,635 --> 01:34:42,885
I wonder if it still works.

1002
01:34:43,261 --> 01:34:46,181
With all those holes in it?

